JOHANNESBURG - Mpumalanga Premier Refilwe Mtsweni-Tsipane says she will ensure the legacy of the late Emalahleni Mayor Lihan Malatjie lives on. Mtsweni-Tsipane was speaking at the funeral service of Malatjie and her husband Sepetlele at the Puma Stadium where mourners gathered to pay their last respects. The couple died in a crash last week while driving on the road between Emalahleni and Kwamhlanga. Mtsweni-Tsipane said the Mpumalanga government would ensure Malatjie's name was forever engrained in people's minds. EMalahleni mayor Linah Malatjie and husband Essau Malatjie were laid to rest today . The couple died in hospital after their car collided with a Ford Ranger bakkie while travelling between KwaMhlanga and Emalahleni. The funeral was attended by Mpumalanga premier. @Emsamo_New pic.twitter.com/tq4MNjCYmQ 